  <description type="morphology">Plants elliptic to globose, ca. 2 mm. Stem leaves cuspidate, broadly channeled;
        laminal cells smooth. Seta short, about 0.3 the diameter of the capsule. Spores spheric to
        elliptic, 30–50 µm, papillose or nearly smooth.</description>
  <description type="morphology">temperate areas of the Northern Hemisphere</description>
  <description type="morphology">Africa.</description>
