  <discussion>Varieties 2 (2 in the flora):</discussion>
  <discussion>As H. A. Crum (1969) and A. J. Grout (1939) pointed out, American specimens reported
        as Acaulon rubrum are A. muticum var. rufescens. These plants are often small, rather
        three-sided and may be confused with A. triquetrum. The leaves of both varieties stain red,
        at least in blotches, in KOH, and they intergrade to some extent.</discussion>
